<paragraph id="20D4CE5BC92CC6ED9DEEDBD750F5110B" pageId="806" pageNumber="807">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="F8ABD6507B8CEBBD39BD881D936B1E74" LSID="44149C91-B2B5-431F-1771-F4A3F6A5D78E" authority="Chaudoir, 1846" authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1846" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Apristus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Apristus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="806" pageNumber="807" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Apristus Chaudoir, 1846</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6F7551B1420F727F8727360A78DD8215" lastPageId="807" lastPageNumber="808" pageId="806" pageNumber="807" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="C08B0F50A3A276F78057FF1D77290C9B" lastPageId="807" lastPageNumber="808" pageId="806" pageNumber="807">
<taxonomicName id="0B8805254EE38BF6228B1BA21FCB4879" authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1846" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Apristus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="806" pageNumber="807" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Apristus</taxonomicName>
Chaudoir [in Chaudoir and Hochhuth], 1846: 62. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="25633E3C0EC7F770EDC1A27F5DCF633D" authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1846" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Apristus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="806" pageNumber="807" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subaeneus">
<emphasis id="1EA84522BAB59DD4301FEDA6C35CB55C" italics="true" pageId="806" pageNumber="807">Apristus subaeneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Chaudoir, 1846 by monotypy. Etymology (original). From the Greek 
<emphasis id="C752424B4E93C6ACB172CA733AB77EB4" italics="true" pageId="806" pageNumber="807">a</emphasis>
<pageBreakToken id="8EF1B4AFBFDC9E951D65ACBF3CF1085C" pageId="807" pageNumber="808" start="start">(</pageBreakToken>
absence) and 
<emphasis id="0E2C85C360F5A34CA9B4F2AD600DCAFA" italics="true" pageId="807" pageNumber="808">prizos</emphasis>
(saw-like), alluding to the smooth (i.e., not denticulate) tarsal claws (&quot; 
<emphasis id="43015672C955B515B0582FA0B41BA175" italics="true" pageId="807" pageNumber="808">
crochets des tarses non 
<normalizedToken id="2D49D18F44722B439AB5640ADF58BCAB" originalValue="dentelÃ©s">denteles</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
&quot;) of the adults [masculine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1284FE67DD39811886DBDF46C6BC82BC" pageId="807" pageNumber="808" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="4D1D36B65350D7B951ABAE5326A39735" pageId="807" pageNumber="808">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="92D1D9F629B909A22514456E70CED054" pageId="807" pageNumber="808">About 60 species (Lorenz 2005: 472) in the Nearctic (13 species), Neotropical (five species in Middle America and the West Indies), Australian, Oriental, Palaearctic (27 species), and Afrotropical Regions.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9AE68221CDD655C9B83D594921411861" pageId="807" pageNumber="808" type="identification">
<paragraph id="D6344BC3E8B3A42366AB75F532F935A1" pageId="807" pageNumber="808">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1FF82D387800E1C87D2ED6F4755FE967" pageId="807" pageNumber="808">
Casey (1920: 272-276) wrote a key to all but one (
<taxonomicName id="F54E51FD383E2684A207FAF613D78991" baseAuthorityName="LeConte" baseAuthorityYear="1846" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Apristus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="807" pageNumber="808" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latens">
<emphasis id="34F9A01819E854B9D739A0A45F86A8BB" italics="true" pageId="807" pageNumber="808">Apristus latens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) North American species. As usual his key is difficult to use. Ten of the current 13 species in North America have been described by Casey (1920) and only two (
<taxonomicName id="5D2D71BF56C6FD743FB1F0CC480B3ABE" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1920" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Apristus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="807" pageNumber="808" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constrictus">
<emphasis id="0920314E0DCF3683B312E08E391FA4D5" italics="true" pageId="807" pageNumber="808">Apristus constrictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D48F1024EB1F437617279EE93469B8BA" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1920" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Apristus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="807" pageNumber="808" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pugetanus">
<emphasis id="0FEA139ADB7BED8FEBFA364EEE7E5C1F" italics="true" pageId="807" pageNumber="808">Apristus pugetanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) have been study subsequently (Lindroth 1969a). A taxonomic revision of the genus is needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
